<TITLE> 49 fire blanks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 15 (bdnews24.com) - In this year's SSC and equivalent examinations, 49 educational institutions fired blank. Of those 49, the Madrasa board had the highest number of 31 institutions that did not have a single candidate pass. The number of such institutions was 72 last year, and 91 in 2008. Education minister Nurul Islam Nahid told a conference on Saturday afternoon that the government would decide later about the institutions which did not have single candidate passing the exams. Of the eight general education boards there were 10 schools that fired blanks. Rajshahi, Comilla and Chittagong did not have a single such school. There was one each from Dhaka and Sylhet, four from Barisal and two from Dinajpur. Under the technical education board, 8 institutions saw all their candidates fail. Nahid said that different steps by the present government, improve the quality of education and thus contributed to reduce the number of institutions that fired blanks. 
